Notice the extra **.json** suffix.

This is happening in zenpy==2.0.1",{},{}
788,IssuesEvent,2016-07-10 04:13:05+00:00,30492678,facetoe/zenpy,1366896,facetoe,,,closed,Retrying on DatabaseDeadlock and DatabaseConflict errors returned by Zendesk,[],[],3,"We sporadically see these errors in our logs:
```
APIException: {""description"": ""Database collision"", ""error"": ""DatabaseConflict""}
```
and
```
APIException: {""description"": ""Database deadlock found; please retry your transaction"", ""error"": ""DatabaseDeadlock""}
```

According to the [docs](https://developer.zendesk.com/rest_api/docs/core/introduction#500-range), the Zendesk API:
>A 503 response with a Retry-After header indicates a database timeout or deadlock. You can retry your request after the number of seconds specified in the Retry-After header.

Do you think zenpy can acknowledge this header and retry the request before raising APIException?",{},{}
