tcp = TCP(dport=53)
dns = DNS(rd=1, qd=DNSQR(qname=fqdn, qtype=rr))

syn = TCP(sport=RandNum(1024,65535),
          dport=tcp.dport,
          flags=""S"",
          seq=42)
synack = sr1(ip/syn)

ack = TCP(sport=synack.dport,
          dport=tcp.dport,
          flags=""A"",
          seq=synack.ack,
          ack=synack.seq + 1)
send(ip/ack)

dnsq = TCP(sport=synack.dport,
           dport=tcp.dport,
           flags=""PA"",
           seq=synack.ack,
           ack=synack.seq + 1)/dns_with_size
dnsr = sr1(ip/dnsq, filter='tcp[13] & 8 != 0')
```

If I look for the DNS layer, it throws an `IndexError: Layer [DNS] not found`, but if I look for the Raw data, it's the expected bytes from the response:

