1378,IssuesEvent,2015-10-07 13:11:45+00:00,21006723,pmorissette/bt,409035,pmorissette,,,closed,Error no module named future,[],[],3,"The new version of ffn which bt uses requires the future module for compatibility between Python 2 & 3. If you used the Anaconda installation for Python and then install bt using ""pip install bt"" when you run bt you get an error no module named future. ""future"" is not in the standard Anaconda packages installed and not loaded when installing bt. Hope this isn't too trivial an issue but it took me a couple of hours to track down.
Using ""conda install future"" fixes the problem.",{},{}
