3065,IssuesEvent,2016-06-07 11:42:16+00:00,36625204,kislyuk/watchtower,1122519,AgDude,,,closed,Flush doesn't work in multiprocessing environment,[],[],2,"I have been trying to implement this log handler for use by Celery workers. Celery creates process forks, but has the appropriate signals when workers start and stop that new handler instances can be started and or stopped to create the necessary threads (and stream names).

Because the child threads are ```daemon=True``` they may be terminated as soon as the flush call is complete, but there is not guarantee that the messages will actually be sent. The flush will exit as soon as the end token comes out of the queue, but the batch has not been submitted yet.
",{},{}
