4557,IssuesEvent,2016-12-01 11:51:38+00:00,4053456,martinblech/xmltodict,2694225,timmwagener,,,opened,Question concerning stable order of *sequence* elements when converted to json lists,[],[],0,"Hello @martinblech ,
I have a quick question concerning the order of xml ``sequence`` elements, when converted to ``json``. 
In short: *Is it stable in any way?*
This kind of stability might be a concern when *diffing* several ``json`` datasets for example with [jsondiff](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/jsondiff)

#### Example data:
----
```xml
<GroupItem attribute_a=""some_value"">
          <Slot attribute_b=""1""/>
          <Slot attribute_b=""2""/>
          <Slot attribute_b=""3""/>
</GroupItem>
```
A guaranteed, stable result in an ideal world would be:
```json
{
    ""GroupItem"": {
        ""@attribute_a"": ""some_value"", 
        ""Slot"": [
            {
                ""@attribute_b"": ""1""
            }, 
            {
                ""@attribute_b"": ""2""
            }, 
            {
                ""@attribute_b"": ""3""
            }
        ]
    }
}
```
Unstable would be like:
```json
...
{
    ""@attribute_b"": ""2""
},
{
    ""@attribute_b"": ""1""
},
...
```",{},{}
