5467,IssuesEvent,2016-05-25 07:49:13+00:00,695611,etianen/django-reversion,6511753,bmarika,,,opened,Does django-reversions support Oauth2 token?,[],[],0,"First of all thanks for the awesome lib.

I am using the django reversion middle ware in my application and I noted that at some point all the ``version[i].revision.user`` was None. Then it hit me that I had switched to token based authentication when I saw the line https://github.com/etianen/django-reversion/blob/master/src/reversion/middleware.py#L33
I did a quick fix by removing the session related checks since on searching the repo, it was only being used at that point. Everything worked well.

What are the implications of removing the session related checks? Can we remove them so as to work seamlessly with token authentication?",{},{}
