6847,IssuesEvent,2017-05-15 19:14:23+00:00,76878964,evenicoulddoit/django-rest-framework-serializer-extensions,3514018,evenicoulddoit,,,closed,Non-model serializers always include method fields,[],[],0,"Non-model serializer, which don't inherit their fields using the `Meta.fields` iterable, automatically take the fields as defined on the class. This means that all `SerializerMethodField`s are included, whether the user intends to expand them or not.

For non-model fields, we'll need to pass over the field definitions, and if not expanded, attempt to pop the field from the list.",{},{}
