7257,IssuesEvent,2016-03-03 19:30:16+00:00,20313056,Yelp/bravado,4341034,lucagiovagnoli,49071,Yelp,opened,BadRequest with form data in Asynchronous client,[],[],0,"I am getting a BadRequest when using form data (only form data Content-type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded, not multi-part).

I managed to reproduce the error and it seems to happen because we are not setting the headers correctly and we are not utf8-encoding the data.
[Here](https://github.com/Yelp/bravado/blob/swaggerpy/swaggerpy/async_http_client.py#L160) we encode the body if the header is set (which is not). In fact we don't set it anywhere:
`
$ ag APP_FORM bravado/
bravado/swaggerpy/async_http_client.py
160:    elif headers.get('content-type') == http_client.APP_FORM:

bravado/swaggerpy/http_client.py
19:APP_FORM = 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded'

bravado/tests/async_http_client_test.py
88:                   'headers': {'content-type': swaggerpy.http_client.APP_FORM}}
`

We should probably do something similar to python ""requests"" which is how the Sync client does it now. Basically they set it like [this](https://github.com/kennethreitz/requests/blob/master/requests/models.py#L454).

Working on a patch to make it work.
",{},{}
