8149,IssuesEvent,2016-08-02 17:49:30+00:00,24774658,boto/boto3,4804047,blrnw3,327752,boto,opened,Loader: add support for loading data files from a zip,[],[],0,"The `Loader` class finds and loads data models. Unfortunately it only works if the data files are in an ordinary directory (because of this check: `if os.path.isdir(path)`)

This means boto is unusable when imported as a zip file.
Here is the loader's search path when you import boto from a zip:
`['/home/ubuntu/.aws/models', '/home/ubuntu/my_zip.zip/botocore/data', '/home/ubuntu/my_zip.zip/boto3/data']`
where `my_zip.zip` contains the result of zipping up the directory after running `pip install boto3 --target=/some/dir`

I'm happy to put in a PR to add zip support if you would be willing to accept it?

P.S.
I need my files in a zip because I'm running jobs on Spark, for which you can specify paths to python files/zips so its executors can use them. It is therefore not possible to use boto within Spark under this workflow.

",{},{}
