8193,IssuesEvent,2015-10-23 21:09:25+00:00,6670942,boto/botocore,54458,catlee,327752,boto,opened,generate_presigned_url doesn't consider expiry time in its cache,[],[],0,"Test code:
```
import boto3

s3 = boto3.client('s3')

print(s3.generate_presigned_url('get_object', {'Bucket': 'foo', 'Key': 'bar'}, ExpiresIn=30, HttpMethod='GET'))
print(s3.generate_presigned_url('get_object', {'Bucket': 'foo', 'Key': 'bar'}, ExpiresIn=86400, HttpMethod='GET'))
```

Results in:
```
https://foo.s3.amazonaws.com/bar?AWSAccessKeyId=AKIAJBPSO2HAGROAJRTA&Expires=1445634402&Signature=INpXclz0bwy2VZq9Lek%2Bbbj93UQ%3D
https://foo.s3.amazonaws.com/bar?AWSAccessKeyId=AKIAJBPSO2HAGROAJRTA&Expires=1445634402&Signature=INpXclz0bwy2VZq9Lek%2Bbbj93UQ%3D
```

Note the same Expires field. I think the problem is in botocore/signers.py, where get_auth() is caching the signature object, but ignoring the expiry time.",{},{}
