8448,IssuesEvent,2015-11-13 20:52:44+00:00,38906603,uber/tchannel-python,41730,abhinav,538264,uber,opened,Get rid of getattr in modules generated with thrift.load.,[],[],0,"This should be fairly trivial. We already iterate through all [services](http://thriftrw.readthedocs.org/en/latest/overview.html#__services__) and `setattr` them on the generated module. The same could be done for [types](http://thriftrw.readthedocs.org/en/latest/overview.html#__types__), [includes](http://thriftrw.readthedocs.org/en/latest/overview.html#__includes__), and [constants](http://thriftrw.readthedocs.org/en/latest/overview.html#__constants__).

Worth noting that these attributes were renamed from `foo` to `__foo__` in 1.0 and `__includes__` is new in 1.0. So the code will have to use some `hasattr`s when doing this.",{},{}
