8622,IssuesEvent,2016-04-04 20:38:28+00:00,12494657,Unidata/siphon,221526,dopplershift,613345,Unidata,closed,Use OrderedDict in catalogs,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Unidata/siphon/labels/Area:%20Catalog', 'name': 'Area: Catalog', 'color': 'c7def8'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Unidata/siphon/labels/Type:%20Enhancement', 'name': 'Type: Enhancement', 'color': 'fad8c7'}]",[],1,"Right now, all key-value stores within `TDSCatalog` are just plain Python `dict`s. It would be better to use `OrderedDict`, so that the order of iteration matches the order we parse in. That, in theory, would eliminate the need sometimes to sort on date/time to get things in proper order, since the server usually puts the most recent first.",{},{}
