8672,IssuesEvent,2018-08-19 12:32:41+00:00,24757484,robotpy/robotpy-wpilib,128854,auscompgeek,640276,robotpy,opened,Update RobotPy for 2019,[],[],0,"Opening this meta-issue early this year for the PyCon AU sprints (next week).

For those of you new to this project, every year we have to update RobotPy's source code to match whatever changes they made to WPILib. It's a bit time consuming and a very manual process.

Last year was a bit of an outlier due to the large changes in WPILib, but in the past we mostly ported things over by the end of October.

We have some tools that help out with this. If you're interested in helping out then check out our porting guide at <http://robotpy.readthedocs.io/en/latest/dev/porting.html>. If the instructions don't make sense, please comment here so we can update them.

Note that the summer hasn't ended in the US yet, and the WPILib team do still have a couple of outstanding projects, so things are still subject to significant change, but I think the bulk of the work has died down now.",{},{}
