9166,IssuesEvent,2017-10-27 01:49:14+00:00,2014929,scikit-image/scikit-image,492549,jni,897180,scikit-image,closed,Region props optimisation (and adding 3D/nD support),"[{'id': 298491707, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-image/scikit-image/labels/type:%20enhancement', 'name': 'type: enhancement', 'color': '51af3c', 'default': False}]",[],5,"Hi all,

Since my main research project uses regionprops to extract image features, I've been more concerned with optimising those functions. I've made a [notebook](http://nbviewer.ipython.org/github/jni/profile-regionprops/blob/master/regionprops-profiling-results.ipynb) with some profiling info. Interestingly, some functions, such as **`bbox`**, appear to suffer quite dramatically from the `@_cached_property` decorator. (I made a [branch](https://github.com/jni/scikit-image/tree/speed-regionprops) to measure this.) Others, like the **convex hull-based properties**, are sort of outside our control so might not be ideal to optimise. Finally, many many features depend on **moments calculation**, so making that 3D and optimising the crap out of it should be fruitful. =)

Thoughts welcome!
",{},{}
9187,IssuesEvent,2016-03-30 19:17:30+00:00,2014929,scikit-image/scikit-image,1315589,soupault,897180,scikit-image,closed,skimage.transform.integral should support nD,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-image/scikit-image/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '51af3c'}]",[],2,"I'll handle this soon if no one steps up. It would automatically make other algorithms easy to convert to nD, including the pending Bradley thresholding (#919).",{},{}
