9477,IssuesEvent,2015-08-17 09:07:50+00:00,2665618,inveniosoftware/invenio,580727,jmartinm,1157480,inveniosoftware,opened,es: ElasticSearch integration improvements,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/t_enhancement', 'name': 't_enhancement', 'color': 'eb6420'}]",[],0,"In the current ElasticSearch integration we have 1 index called `records` and inside a document type called `record`. In order to be production ready, these are some changes that can be introduced:

* [ ] Allow separating document types in different indexes. This will make our integration [ES 2.0 ready and avoid conflicts in mappings](https://www.elastic.co/blog/great-mapping-refactoring) between different document types.

* [ ] Use aliases instead of indexes for zero downtime (https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/guide/current/index-aliases.html).

* [ ] Allow each overlay to have its own mappings. Currently, the mapping is [hardcoded is `es.py`](https://github.com/inveniosoftware/invenio/blob/master/invenio/ext/es.py)",{},{}
9490,IssuesEvent,2017-03-23 08:55:18+00:00,2665618,inveniosoftware/invenio,656365,krzysztof,1157480,inveniosoftware,opened,RFC new Invenio module for easy building of end-user CLI applications,[],[],0,"As part of Google Summer of Code we are considering to build a CLI tool for Zenodo as one of the possible projects (see the details [HERE](https://github.com/zenodo/zenodo/wiki/Google-Summer-of-Code-2017#zenodo-cli)). Basically the Idea is to create a simple pip-installable utility for Zenodo which will allow end-users to perform simple REST actions without the need to reading through or understanding of the REST API. Basically it's a command-line wrapper around the REST calls.

One of the ""extra"" requirements of this GSoC project is to create this as a generic Invenio module, which can be configured by an overlay to easily create an overlay-specific CLI. Although writing an overlay specific is quite straightforward, making a configurable, clean and generic module might require some extra thoughts.

Interested student @rusrushal13 and probably many others interested in this project wanted to reach out to Invenio community to gather some more intel on:

a) Would any other service be interested in such tool for their userbase / do you have something in place already?
b) Any feedback on the idea? Any roadblocks you can see with making it generic module?",{},{}
9494,IssuesEvent,2015-02-17 10:02:35+00:00,2665618,inveniosoftware/invenio,119349,kaplun,1157480,inveniosoftware,opened,session: remove CFG_WEBSESSION_DIFFERENTIATE_BETWEEN_GUESTS,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/c_WebSession', 'name': 'c_WebSession', 'color': 'ededed'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/next', 'name': 'next', 'color': 'd4c5f9'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/p_minor', 'name': 'p_minor', 'color': 'f7c6c7'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/RFC', 'name': 'RFC', 'color': '009800'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/t_debt', 'name': 't_debt', 'color': 'eb6420'}]",[],0,"```python
## CFG_WEBSESSION_DIFFERENTIATE_BETWEEN_GUESTS -- when set to 1, the session
## system allocates the same uid=0 to all guests users regardless of where they
## come from. 0 allocate a unique uid to each guest.
CFG_WEBSESSION_DIFFERENTIATE_BETWEEN_GUESTS = 0
```

In modern Flask time, if one wants to store some session related data for a guest user, should better do it in a cookie. This functionality had been implemented in the past in order to showcase certain Invenio functionalities (baskets, alerts) to guests users, without requiring them to login.

In modern time it is socially acceptable to require authentication to use user oriented functionalities of an online service.

So this RFC is to propose the removal of such configuration piece (thus simplifying the session/authentication/authorization stack).",{},{}
