9628,IssuesEvent,2017-02-22 10:39:18+00:00,8411798,zopefoundation/ExtensionClass,483109,hannosch,1163184,zopefoundation,closed,Py_TPFLAGS_HAVE_CLASS in ExtensionClass.h,[],"[{'login': 'stephan-hof', 'id': 620934, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/620934?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stephan-hof', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/stephan-hof', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stephan-hof/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stephan-hof/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stephan-hof/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stephan-hof/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stephan-hof/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stephan-hof/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stephan-hof/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stephan-hof/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stephan-hof/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",3,"The ``PyMem_DEL`` macro in ExtensionClass.h uses `Py_TPFLAGS_HAVE_CLASS` unconditionally on both Python 2 and 3, though it's always true and gone in Python 3. Our `_compat.h` file has a helper macro `HAS_TP_DESCR_GET` for the same check, which should probably be used:

```
#define PyMem_DEL(O)                                   \
  if ((Py_TYPE(O)->tp_flags & Py_TPFLAGS_HAVE_CLASS) \
      && (Py_TYPE(O)->tp_free != NULL))              \
    Py_TYPE(O)->tp_free((PyObject*)(O));             \
  else                                                 \
    PyObject_FREE((O));
```

I'm just not sure if `ExtensionClass.h` should include `_compat.h` now or if there's some problem with that. Or if maybe more of this macro could be avoided under Python 3.",{},{}
