9815,IssuesEvent,2016-12-30 16:59:24+00:00,31666852,spyder-ide/qtawesome,365293,ccordoba12,1284937,spyder-ide,closed,App freezes upon importing qtawesome,[],[],3,"For some reason just importing qtawesome seems to freeze my python script entirely. I can't even stop it with Ctrl+C, I have to use Task Manager to kill it.

The file I'm running is only this:
```python
import sys
from PyQt5.QtWidgets import QApplication
app = QApplication(sys.argv)
import qtawesome as qta
```

[Here](http://pastebin.com/jvuskwY0) is the result of running `python -v testscript.py`. You can see it imports `qtawesome\__init__.py` at line 135, then starts loading a bunch of PyQt modules, then finally freezes at the end on loading `PyQt5.QtWebEngineCore`.

I'm not really sure what to make of this. Let me know if I might be doing something to cause this.",{},{}
9822,IssuesEvent,2017-02-23 19:26:48+00:00,5075775,keenlabs/KeenClient-Python,5125595,clarkenciel,1315418,keenlabs,opened,Install through pip fails due to VERSION and REAMDE.rst file reads,[],[],0,"Trying to install keen through pip fails. `setup.py` is unable to find VERSION or README.rst. This seems to be related to how and where pip runs a package's setup.py script.

The line [here](https://github.com/keenlabs/KeenClient-Python/blob/master/setup.py#L29) is the culprit: the VERSION file cannot be found in whatever directory pip is calling the script from.

[This line](https://github.com/keenlabs/KeenClient-Python/blob/master/setup.py#L36) also seems to fail for a similar reason.

Here is the pip error for the VERSION failure:
```
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""/tmp/pip-install-test/keen/setup.py"", line 29, in <module>
    version_file = open(os.path.join('.', 'VERSION'))
FileNotFoundError: [Errno 2] No such file or directory: './VERSION'
```

Here is the pip error for the README failure (which occurs after fixing the VERSION failure):
```
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""/tmp/pip-install-test/keen/setup.py"", line 36, in <module>
    long_description=codecs.open(os.path.join('README.rst'), 'r', encoding='UTF-8').read(),
  File ""/usr/lib/python3.6/codecs.py"", line 895, in open
    file = builtins.open(filename, mode, buffering)
FileNotFoundError: [Errno 2] No such file or directory: 'README.rst'
```",{},{}
