9828,IssuesEvent,2015-04-17 15:56:36+00:00,19978672,mollie/mollie-api-python,9683084,Lexstok,1327170,mollie,opened,os.path.dirname(__file__) returns empty,[],[],0,"In the examples there are 2 examples for writing to the so-called database (in this case, generate a text file). This did not work on windows (perhaps this has nothing to do with this being on windows, but more todo with looking into the current directory), I had to change the code from
    os.path.dirname(__file__)
