10164,IssuesEvent,2015-04-07 01:23:12+00:00,3510804,GalSim-developers/GalSim,1454906,rmandelb,1462196,GalSim-developers,closed,WFIRST module,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/GalSim-developers/GalSim/labels/module', 'name': 'module', 'color': '02e10c'}]",[],60,"This issue is similar in flavor to #556, but I'm interested in working on this one first.  The idea is to make a WFIRST module.  Comments on any of the below are welcome:

(1) Bandpasses: I would like there to be routines to get Bandpass objects for the planned WFIRST bandpasses, i.e.
```
my_bandpass = galsim.wfirst.getBandpass(...)
```
where the argument might be a string that is the name of the bandpass.  An alternative would be to make a routine that returns all bandpass info, e.g., 
```
bandpass_list = galsim.wfirst.getBandpasses()
```
where it returns a list of tuples, each containing the name of the bandpass and the associated Bandpass object.

(2) WCS information for the chips, similar to what's described on #556.

(3) PSF information.  I need to dig a bit more into what information I have before deciding how to put this in.  Will probably post some thoughts once I've done that.

(4) Information about various detector effects such as those discussed in #552, #553, #554, #555.  My assumption is that the code to apply those effects will not be in a WFIRST module, but rather in a GalSim ""detectors"" (or something) module, but presumably those routines will require inputs like the function defining nonlinearity, the type of kernel to apply to simulate inter pixel capacitance, etc.  So the WFIRST module needs to know those things about the WFIRST detectors, to provide inputs for anyone who wants to use the routines in the ""detectors"" module to make WFIRST-y detector effects.

Any comments or suggestions?",{},{}
