10838,IssuesEvent,2016-01-19 15:39:14+00:00,15510233,openfisca/openfisca-france,12686,cbenz,1794404,openfisca,opened,Make parameters merge script reentrant,[],[],0,"This follows a discussion with @benjello, @MalkIPP and @laem.

The script [`merge_ipp_tax_and_benefit_tables_with_parameters.py`](https://github.com/openfisca/openfisca-france/blob/baremes-ipp/openfisca_france/scripts/merge_ipp_tax_and_benefit_tables_with_parameters.py) is not reentrant (if I modify for instance [`isf.xml`](https://github.com/openfisca/openfisca-france/blob/baremes-ipp/openfisca_france/parameters/isf.xml) and re-execute the script, the modifications should be kept).

This would prevent the projets like Mes aides to contribute in XLS files.

Note: for now it is possible to contribute in `param.xml` which is read by the script, but it constrains the contributor to know the mapping (`param-to-parameters.yaml`) and apply it backwards, to find the old parameter name starting from a formula.

@eraviart Would it be difficult to make the script reentrant?",{},{}
