11067,IssuesEvent,2016-10-13 16:29:59+00:00,4322486,pretenders/pretenders,17954127,system7ltd,2529783,pretenders,opened,"Allow HTTPMock.reply() to use a callable as ""body"" in order to generate dynamic responses upon each request",[],[],0,"Hello, I thought such a feature could be very useful.  Here is an example usage scenario:

/films returns a list of films, each film has a date associated with it.  Now let us say that the system should allow to filter films by date and let the user go to /films?before=1970&after=1940 or /films?before=1950.  Let us say we want to be able to test all combinations of before and after for the following values [None, 1950, 1970, 2000, 2015] and we have a fixture with seven films.  That gives us 25 different requests.  We could, of course, generate when().reply() presets/rules programmatically but I cannot help but feel that it would be much more elegant (and practical) to just pass a callable to reply() as body and each time a request is made, run the callable(request) to generate the body.  

What do you think?",{},{}
