```
TypeError: 'NoneType' object is not iterable
```

Does db.py support the TRUNCATE command?",{},{}
11138,IssuesEvent,2016-03-18 15:08:19+00:00,24213271,adobe-type-tools/afdko,93914,khaledhosny,2768660,adobe-type-tools,opened,[spec] size parameters description is not clear,[],[],0,"The description of the size feature parameters is not very clear, namely:

> These values may also be specified more directly as decimal point values

It is not clear which values can be decimal point, all the four or only the decipoints ones? (my guess which makes since, but it was not clear the first, and even the second times I read the description).

> but a decimal point and following value is then required.

This not clear either, does this mean `parameters 10.0 0;` is accepted, but `parameters 10;` is not? If so, why?

Also it is not explicitly mentioned which value can be omitted and what the default will be.

(for the background I’m adding size feature support to FontTools, behdad/fonttools#550, and had to go to many iterations and still not sure my implementation is right).",{},{}
