11696,IssuesEvent,2016-07-12 16:07:23+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,7378,baroquebobcat,3065172,pantsbuild,closed,Native data types for subprocesses,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/engine', 'name': 'engine', 'color': 'fbca04'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/engine-codegen', 'name': 'engine-codegen', 'color': 'fef2c0'}]","[{'login': 'baroquebobcat', 'id': 7378, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7378?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/baroquebobcat', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/baroquebobcat', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/baroquebobcat/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/baroquebobcat/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/baroquebobcat/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/baroquebobcat/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/baroquebobcat/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/baroquebobcat/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/baroquebobcat/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/baroquebobcat/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/baroquebobcat/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",2,"This would be a set of native data types for a process execution, using our existing ProcessManager infrastructure, but encapsulated as a Node.

To request execution of a process, a task would use a Selector subclass specific to that Node type with all of the necessary inputs and specifying a Glob to match files captured from a chroot where the process had been run. The task would then receive some sort of result Struct holding the FileContents from the execution.",{},{}
11705,IssuesEvent,2015-11-08 13:29:47+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,119728,ericzundel,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,Make parsing list options more tolerant to whitespace (and quoting?),[],[],0,"I like using `action=append` type of arguments just because they are easy to specify on the command line.  An append argument you just pass a single element of the list with an argument value and it keeps appending to an existing list.

There's been talk of getting rid of append, because you can't use it to override something already specified as a default elsewhere.  I think I'm OK with that, but  for command line usages,  I find list type options tricky to get right.  A typical command line session for me:

```
./pants compile service/exemplar --cache-read-from=""http://com.example/foo""
Nope:
Exception message: The value cannot be evaluated as a literal expression: invalid syntax (<string>, line 1)
Given raw value:
1: http://com.example/foo
```

Oh wait it is a list:

```
./pants compile service/exemplar --cache-read-from=[http://com.example/foo]
Nope:
Exception message: The value cannot be evaluated as a literal expression: invalid syntax (<string>, line 1)
Given raw value:
1: [http://com.example/foo]

```

OK, look at the help:

```
./pants help cache --cache-advanced
...
---cache-read-from=""['str1','str2',...]"" (default: ['https://pypi.corp.squareup.com/laundrybasket/'])
    The URIs of artifact caches to read directly from. Each entry is a URL of a
    RESTful cache, a path of a filesystem cache, or a pipe-separated list of
    alternate caches to choose from. This list is also used as input to the
    resolver. When resolver is 'none' list is used as is.
```

Maybe I need to quote something

```
$ ./pants compile service/exemplar --cache-read-from=['http://com.example/foo']  --cache-read

Nope
Exception message: The value cannot be evaluated as a literal expression: invalid syntax (<string>, line 1)
Given raw value:
1: [http://com.example/foo]
```

Huh, I know config.ini is picky about spaces:
```
$ ./pants compile service/exemplar --cache-read-from=""[ 'http://com.example/foo' ]""  --cache-read

Nope:
Unknown goals: ]
Use `pants goals` to list goals.
Use `pants help` to get help.
```

Finally this works:
```
./pants compile service/exemplar --cache-read-from=""['http://com.example/foo']""  --cache-read
```",{},{}
11707,IssuesEvent,2016-01-19 22:17:56+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,5316293,digwanderlust,3065172,pantsbuild,reopened,"Add a Task 'implementation version', to allow Task implementers to invalidate artifacts","[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/1.0.0', 'name': '1.0.0', 'color': 'c7def8'}]",[],4,"The implementation version would be a (string) property of a Task that a Task implementer could use to invalidate all artifacts for the Task.

Additionally, in the case of `Task.incremental==True`, the implementation version should be used to skip incrementalism. The easiest way to do this would likely be to include the current implementation version in the `results_dir` path, and to _not_ persist it in the build invalidator.",{},{}
