11752,IssuesEvent,2015-02-03 22:25:30+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,119728,ericzundel,3065172,pantsbuild,closed,pants goal run fails on codegen examples,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}]",[],4,"Discovered when trying to write integration tests for protobuf; I thought it was a problem with my code, but after much investigation it seems that the recent RoundManager refactor has stopped 'compile' occurring before 'run'.

This can be reproduced on the current master branch (33e2b0c47bb30080575f44ef3082a4b6f65414ae as of writing), and running goal clean-all followed by any of:

./pants goal run src/java/com/pants/examples/jaxb/main
./pants goal run src/java/com/pants/examples/protobuf
./pants goal run src/java/com/pants/examples/annotation/main
(with PANTS_DEV=1 of course)

In contrast, all of these targets work as expected when I run ./pants goal bundle, and execute the jar manually.

The phase execution order for running is: bootstrap -> gen -> check-exclusives -> run

The phase execution order for bundling is: bootstrap -> gen -> check-exclusives -> resolve -> compile -> resources -> bundle

./pants goal compile run fails differently, with ""'NoneType' object has no attribute 'get_group_key_for_target'"" in ""jvm_run.py"".

./pants goal compile works by itself after cleaning, but following it with a ./pants goal run (without cleaning) fails executing java with a 'could not find or load main class ...'.

This was all in a new folder with a freshly checked out version of the repo.",{},{}
