anforth/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/lauradanforth/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}, {'login': 'khangmach', 'id': 25045166, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/25045166?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/khangmach', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/khangmach', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/khangmach/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/khangmach/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/khangmach/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/khangmach/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/khangmach/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/khangmach/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/khangmach/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/khangmach/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/khangmach/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}, {'login': 'laurenlichtman', 'id': 25990164, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/25990164?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/laurenlichtman', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/laurenlichtman', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/laurenlichtman/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/laurenlichtman/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/laurenlichtman/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/laurenlichtman/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/laurenlichtman/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/laurenlichtman/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/laurenlichtman/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/laurenlichtman/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/laurenlichtman/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}, {'login': 'navakk9', 'id': 26124065, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/26124065?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/navakk9', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/navakk9', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/navakk9/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/navakk9/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/navakk9/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/navakk9/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/navakk9/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/navakk9/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/navakk9/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/navakk9/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/navakk9/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",15,"## Summary

A long-needed change. Thanks to @laurenlichtman for bringing it up.

**Current order of the content recommendation subsections:**

1. Most popular
2. Next steps
3. Resume
4. Overview (to be renamed)

**Proposed reordering:**

1. Resume
2. Next steps
3. Most popular
4. Overview (to be renamed)

**Justification:**
Presenting ""Resume"" followed by ""Next steps"" is more in line with supporting a personalized learning experience. The Learner would see content that is most related to what they were most recently engaging with first, without needing to scroll or click through a labyrinth of topics.

Please write comments providing further justifications for either ordering, as there is not consensus in the team for the proposed reordering.

## System information

*Please specify the Kolibri version you were using and your operating system!*

 - Version: Kolibri 0.5.0beta1.dev33
 - Operating system: MacOS Sierra
 - Browser: Chrome
",{},{}
12029,IssuesEvent,2017-09-25 09:16:04+00:00,49976939,learningequality/kolibri,13453618,harishbalachandran,3926525,learningequality,opened,<Imp Enhancement> Learner username is not displayed on the top right corner of the browser on a Portrait mode in a tablet.,[],[],0,"## Summary
Learner username is not displayed on the top right corner of the browser on a Portrait mode in a tablet.

When the tablet is key in landscape mode the learners can see their logged in username on the top right corner, but when you switch it to portrait mode learner's login ID is not visible and on top of that he/she cannot know who's ID he is logged in, as the username is not visible on the dropdown option on the top right corner.

**Important user story**
Its always good to have the learners name displayed all times at the top right corner, so that the learner is aware that he/she is using their own account. This is a big issue since we have't implemented the #2131 and because of this at-least 50% of the leaner end up progressing on the wrong student account. Some learners prefer using Portrait mode and some prefer Landscape mode, hence is enhancement is important.

## System information
 - Version: 0.4.5 and 0.5.0
 - Operating system: Ubuntu 14.04LTS
 - Browser: Chrome.

## How to reproduce
1. Login in a tablet on Landscape mode, notice the user name is clearly visible at the top right corner.
2. Now switch to Portrait mode and notice the username is not visible and not found in the dropdown too.
3. The learner has to got to profiles to know the username.

## Screenshots
On landscape mode:
![img_20170919_162516](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/13453618/30801189-113b35f2-a200-11e7-891e-68111c2b5ea2.jpg)

On Portrait mode:
![img_20170919_162503](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/13453618/30801195-1a3cdd40-a200-11e7-9d88-89d5f498ecb6.jpg)



## Real-life consequences (anything community should be aware of, for instance how it affects your deployment)
Learner's end up using the wrong user accounts most of the time. Consequence is  👎  :)",{},{}
12038,IssuesEvent,2017-12-04 17:16:04+00:00,49976939,learningequality/kolibri,2367265,indirectlylit,3926525,learningequality,closed,import/export: unlisted channels are not persisted,"[{'id': 667034823, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/learningequality/kolibri/labels/P1', 'name': 'P1', 'color': 'FFAB4A', 'default': False}]",[],7,"### Observed behavior

users need to re-enter secret tokens or channel IDs every time they go back to import new content or update

### Expected behavior

""unlocked"" channels should be persisted after unlocking them. They should [show up in the channel selection list](https://projects.invisionapp.com/share/Q9D1VQD67#/screens/254175319) with a 'lock' icon:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2367265/33354840-a505e0d4-d469-11e7-9f7c-6552b4b8412e.png)


### User-facing consequences

user needs to unnecessarily re-enter tokens/ids

### Steps to reproduce

* start with no channels
* import from internet
* enter a channel ID
* import a subset of the channel
* go back to the beginning, and try to import more items. you need to re-enter the ID

### Context

* Kolibri version: 0.7-beta

-----

cc @jonboiser
",{},{}
12056,IssuesEvent,2017-12-06 05:13:47+00:00,49976939,learningequality/kolibri,2367265,indirectlylit,3926525,learningequality,opened,fix historic migrations to be Py2/3 compatible,[],[],0,"### Observed behavior

