12071,IssuesEvent,2017-03-24 00:36:31+00:00,49976939,learningequality/kolibri,2367265,indirectlylit,3926525,learningequality,closed,Allow plugins to be built standalone,"[{'id': 492822760, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/learningequality/kolibri/labels/DEV:%20backend', 'name': 'DEV: backend', 'color': 'DFDFDF', 'default': False}, {'id': 493378585, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/learningequality/kolibri/labels/DEV:%20devops', 'name': 'DEV: devops', 'color': 'DFDFDF', 'default': False}, {'id': 492821376, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/learningequality/kolibri/labels/DEV:%20frontend', 'name': 'DEV: frontend', 'color': 'DFDFDF', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'aronasorman', 'id': 191955, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/191955?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/aronasorman', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/aronasorman', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/aronasorman/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/aronasorman/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/aronasorman/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/aronasorman/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/aronasorman/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/aronasorman/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/aronasorman/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/aronasorman/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/aronasorman/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}, {'login': 'rtibbles', 'id': 1680573, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/1680573?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rtibbles', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/rtibbles', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rtibbles/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rtibbles/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rtibbles/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rtibbles/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rtibbles/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rtibbles/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rtibbles/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rtibbles/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rtibbles/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",4,"## Summary

Right now, looks like we need to clone both a Kolibri repository and the specific plugin we need to build, and then run the devserver to have it serve the assets. It's hard on a devops and CI perspective to start building the plugins:

- Which version of Kolibri do I need to clone to get a plugin building? We'll like to pin a plugin to a version of Kolibri in the long term.
- I'm basically just replicating the Kolibri build pipeline, but with one small change. This consumes both devops and computing resources.
- What specific steps should I take to get a plugin building and releasable? Right now, the plugin build process is very dev-focused. Hence I'm having a hard time to figure out what steps I need to do on a continuous integration perspective. `yarn install && yarn run build`, `pip install -e && make assets` all are no dice. Running `make dist` inside the plugin itself doesn't work too.

## Possible solutions

The goal is to have `make dist` produce a working `whl` file that's ready to be uploaded to PyPI.

1. When `make dist` is run, clone Kolibri on Git based on a certain tag, and then run `yarn run build` or some other magic using the cloned Kolibri dir. `make clean` should remove said directory.
1. Similar to the one above, but only fetch the exact files that are needed to build. So maybe only the vue files and the frontend build dependencies?
1. Make the plugin fully standalone (has all the dependencies needed to build its assets). Not sure what this would involve, but is the cleanest solution.

",{},{}
