I have a question about how to best deal with unicode control characters. 

We're retrieving results from the Adwords API, but unfortunately, some of them contain '0x10' as a character which breaks the XML parsing of the entire response. Since we're doing this for a variety of reports we don't control, we'd ideally like to strip out these sorts of characters, or at least handle it gracefully (via a flag or otherwise).

