12230,IssuesEvent,2017-12-13 19:39:08+00:00,12898486,juju/charm-tools,406082,johnsca,4604548,juju,opened,wheelhouse.txt is only additive,"[{'id': 270572531, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/juju/charm-tools/labels/charm-build', 'name': 'charm-build', 'color': 'eb6420', 'default': False}]",[],0,"When building a charm, there is no way to actually override a dependency in `wheelhouse.txt`.  New entries instead simply add to the wheelhouse and at install time they are installed according to lexicographical ordering.  While this usually ends up with the desired result, it fails if you need to pin something to an older version and inflates the wheelhouse and thus the charm.

To address this, we will need to parse the wheelhouse entries at build time and ensure that we do the right thing.",{},{}
