12856,IssuesEvent,2015-04-30 05:12:49+00:00,11589713,deis/deis,536009,carmstrong,6117407,deis,reopened,"Azure: Investigate Router ""[emerg] 16#0: bind() to 0.0.0.0:2222 failed (98: Address already in use)""",[],[],10,"On Azure, and sometimes on Vagrant, I see the error:

``` [emerg] 16#0: bind() to 0.0.0.0:2222 failed (98: Address already in use) ```

on the router process.

With a multiple router setup (3 for 5 boxes for example), one failing causes certain processes e.g. ``` deis ps:list ``` to return ```503``.

Right now, I haven't found any other processes using port 2222 aside from Azure opening port 2222 to the public, I'm unsure what else is using this point on the host.

My best guess currently is that another instance of router attempted to start up and caused the collision - but I have no actual proof of that yet.

Logs of two recent malfunctioning router issues in a three router cluster:
[router@1](https://www.dropbox.com/s/h4k45xd4633s5bk/router_1.log?dl=0)
[router@2](https://www.dropbox.com/s/udva3li48wq0i3b/router_2.log?dl=0)

I'm going to try and carve out some time to look into this more deeply.",{},{}
12857,IssuesEvent,2015-02-24 03:03:59+00:00,11589713,deis/deis,968339,phspagiari,6117407,deis,opened,Proposal: LDAP/AD auth on controller,[],[],0,"As we discussed at #1578, in order to use deis at large companies we need a way to use LDAP authentications on deis. 

I would be happy if I start to contribute with deis using this idea, indeed I already tested some ideas, but it will be very good if some of the core developers help me with the design of the idea making easy to use and administer.

So far I learned about how integrate ldap with django and already tested with a simple authentication app in django, so far so good.
Now I want to implement this on the controller and extend the configuration to etcd + deis client since the ldap configs are located in settings.py of the controller.

My idea is something like this:

 - django-auth-ldap, ldap and python-etcd as requirements of deis-controller.
 - Add LDAP settings into settings.py of controller and getting all values of attibutes from etcd.
 - Activating the LDAP with something like this:

```shell
deisctl config ldap set host=ldap.domain.com
deisctl config ldap set dn=""dc=ldap,dc=domain""
deisctl config ldap set user-search=""ou=Users,dc=my""
deisctl config ldap set group-search=""ou=Groups""
```
or

```shell
deisctl config platform set ldap=""ldap://ldap.domain.com:ou=Groups,ou=Users,dc=my,dc=ldap,dc=domain""
```

- The user will make a register with the user/password of LDAP and the register will make a verification if ldap is enabled and instead of creating a new user he will make a copy (avoiding that every time when the user makes login the controller go to de LDAP to authenticate the user).
- The user will be replicated in deis users database.
- The user will make a normal login, receive the token (now with a expiration time)

I really dont know if this is a good implementation, so lets discuss about this before we start to implement.",{},{}
12871,IssuesEvent,2016-04-02 17:33:59+00:00,11589713,deis/deis,50034,rosstimson,6117407,deis,opened,Support ssh keys larger than 4096 on Workflow (v2),[],[],0,"I'm a Deis n00b but I'm testing out the v2 (Workflow) beta and when it came to trying to add my ssh key with `deis keys:add` I encountered:

