13233,IssuesEvent,2015-11-05 21:54:19+00:00,846444,Blosc/bcolz,76716,grahamc,6469856,Blosc,opened,Cannot be installed with Numpy 1.10 due to incorrect package comparison operator,[],[],0,"Hi, installing `bcolz` with Anaconda 2.4.0 fails. Anaconda 2.4.0 ships Numpy 1.10.1. Numerically, 1.10 is less than 1.7, but version-wise it is greater. Unfortunately `bcolz` uses an invalid comparison operator: 

https://github.com/Blosc/bcolz/blob/2851981f220b8a4dbc8c63ddede8e1f6dac0380c/pavement.py#L82

In short:

```
>>> '1.9.2' > '1.7'
True
>>> '1.10' > '1.7'
False
>>> '1.10.1' > '1.7'
False
```",{},{}
