13520,IssuesEvent,2016-01-28 23:53:26+00:00,4127088,Azure/azure-sdk-for-python,108494,bear454,6844498,Azure,opened,Can't access disconnected regions with ASM,[],[],0,"https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-python/blob/master/azure-servicemanagement-legacy/azure/servicemanagement/constants.py#L27 defines one specific hostname for API access. This effectively blocks use of the SDK for disconnected regions with their own API endpoints, like China East & China North.

The publishsettings file includes a management endpoint reference ( /PublishData/PublishProfile/Subscription/ServiceManagementUrl ), that could be used instead (like the nodejs tools); or a general mapping could be made of Azure regions to endpoints, e.g. `'West US' => 'management.core.windows.net', 'China North' => 'management.core.chinacloudapi.cn'`.

As it stands though, I don't see any possible way to access disconnected regions.",{},{}
