13647,IssuesEvent,2016-12-07 09:59:32+00:00,17714713,pre-commit/pre-commit-hooks,5459009,lavish205,6943086,pre-commit,opened,[Question] why can't we add pylint in this repo hooks.yaml file?,[],[],0,"My `.pre-commit-config.yaml` file looks like this:
```yaml
-   repo: https://github.com/pre-commit/pre-commit-hooks
     sha: 52582865ab7ed8f41734253190844c854ddd9a9e
     hooks:
     -   id: trailing-whitespace
     -   id: check-ast
     -   id: debug-statements
     -   id: end-of-file-fixer
-   repo: git://github.com/pre-commit/mirrors-pylint
     sha: v1.6.4
     hooks:
    -   id: pylint
```
and when I run `pre-commit install` it creates a repo for pylint in `~/.pre-commit/repoXXXX/` with its own virtual env in it, due to which pylint shows `import errors`.
So there are two ways to solve this error:

1. add all required packages in `additional_dependencies` in `.pre-commit-config.yaml` file for pylint.
But I can't add all the packages here because it useless to create two virtual env with same packages.
Can we however, merge it with our own virtualenv??

2. if I modify `pre-commit-hooks/hooks.yaml` and add pylint hook over there, it works perfectly fine.

Can you suggest me which is the best way to do it??",{},{}
13650,IssuesEvent,2018-06-13 15:34:16+00:00,17714713,pre-commit/pre-commit-hooks,1810591,asottile,6943086,pre-commit,closed,Unexpect behavior with flake8 hook?,[],[],2,"Considering a python package repository using `setup.cfg` and with the `flake8` pre-commit hook installed, when a person adds a `[flake8]` section to the `setup.cfg` file, with an `exclude` option, this person would naturally expects that the commit hook ignores the files/directories listed...

However, since pre-commit sends as arguments a list of changed files, this configuration is somehow neglected, and flake8 lints the excluded files anyway...

So if we run `pre-commit run flake8 -a`, we end up with a different result then just running `flake8`.

Is this behavior expected/documented somewhere?

I have create an example repository to make it easy to reproduce:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/abravalheri/dummy-pre-commit-example-for-issue
cd dummy-pre-commit-example-for-issue
grep ""\[flake8\]"" setup.cfg -A 9  # --> Check the configuration
pre-commit install
flake8  # --> results more or less expected by the user
pre-commit run flake8 -a  # --> different from the previous results
```

Any tips about this?",{},{}
13668,IssuesEvent,2016-10-31 06:25:37+00:00,1605598,bulletphysics/bullet3,7190873,BluePrintRandom,6955508,bulletphysics,reopened,Compound physics Armature Actors,[],[],4,"So I have found an easy way to get an accurate physics shape for actors in blender

I have a compound root object - the armature to be animated parents to this,
each bone that is to have physics has a 'bone tag' parented to it, and a shild shape
that approximates the shape of the bone

every frame I remove parent on all the child shapes, move them to where the bone tag is, and match it's rotation, then compound parent the child shape to the root,

this allows my actors to go up and down stairs by applying a forward servo motion while playing a stair walk animation.

this system works great, but when a child shape is contacting, and is moved, produces no friction,

I purpose a build in system that does all this under the hood but also computes the friction during the move maybe using substeps?

here is the system in action - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cx_9F0RNtzc
however she will not walk forward only by playing an animation - I have to combine the animation with a forward sero motion.
",{},{}
