14530,IssuesEvent,2017-07-21 11:17:41+00:00,5362370,pytest-dev/pytest-rerunfailures,2048203,dangercrow,8897583,pytest-dev,opened,Fixtures marked (scope='session') are run on every re-run,[],[],0,"I would expect that session fixtures are run once per session - but it seems if a `flaky` test reruns, it will run session scoped fixtures' teardown code, and then their setup again.

This can result in costly setup/teardown being unnecessarily rerun, and also seems to go against the whole point of labelling the fixture `session`

Reproduction:

```Python
@pytest.fixture(scope=""session"")
def example_fixture():
    print(""\nSetup"")
    yield
    print(""Teardown"")

@pytest.mark.flaky(reruns=1)
def test_example_fixture(example_fixture):
    assert 0
```

Running with `pytest -s -v ...` I get:

```
plugins: timeout-1.2.0, rerunfailures-2.2, repeat-0.4.1, ordering-0.5
collected 1 items 

scripts/autotest/tests/conftest.py::test_example_fixture 
Setup
Teardown
RERUN
scripts/autotest/tests/conftest.py::test_example_fixture 
Setup
Teardown
FAILED
```",{},{}
