14786,IssuesEvent,2016-01-28 22:55:39+00:00,26516210,letsencrypt/letsencrypt,1750103,schoen,9289019,letsencrypt,opened,Error that results when run without root is unclear,[],[],0,"When running `letsencrypt` without root, I get

```
An unexpected error occurred:
OSError: [Errno 13] Permission denied: '/etc/letsencrypt'
Please see the logfile 'letsencrypt.log' for more details.
```

The underlying reason is that, to run without root, I need to specify `--config-dir`, `--work-dir`, and `--log-dir`. However, the client doesn't give me any suggestion about this or about the possibility of doing anything (even reading help) without root access.

While a sysadmin would probably conclude that the reason for the `OSError` is simply that the client needs root to run, it would be great to have a clearer and more useful error message in this case.",{},{}
