14889,IssuesEvent,2016-04-01 18:56:59+00:00,26876372,dateutil/dateutil,24827,svetlyak40wt,9849410,dateutil,opened,Parsing ISO date is broken when dayfirst=True (since 2.5.2 release),[],[],0,"Before 2.5.2 release, parse with dayfirst=True, parsed dates like '2015-02-06' as expected 2 – month and 06 – day. This is right, because `-` delimiter is only possible in ISO 8601. According to this list: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Date_format_by_country, format yyyy-dd-mm is not used anywhere.

Seems, pull request https://github.com/dateutil/dateutil/pull/229 broken this behavior.

Can we please fix it, because I need to parse '2015-02-06' as 6 February, but if date was given as 06.02.15 consider first number is a day.",{},{}
