14980,IssuesEvent,2017-04-17 20:29:43+00:00,552926,django-ckeditor/django-ckeditor,1822699,riklaunim,9961418,django-ckeditor,closed,404s when using ManifestFilesMixin,[],[],5,"I recently implemented the ManifestFilesMixin for my static files storage in my project. Everything works fine, but when ckeditor inits, it tries to load config.js and gets a 404. I'm having a hard time pinpointing where the issue is - either the staticfiles side in django, or in the the ckeditor.js itself.

The way I was able to bypass the problem was to update the staticfiles.json file to remove the hash from the ckeditor.js location: 
""ckeditor/ckeditor/ckeditor.js"": ""ckeditor/ckeditor/ckeditor.356423a8692e.js""
to
""ckeditor/ckeditor/ckeditor.js"": ""ckeditor/ckeditor/ckeditor.js""

I'm not really sure why this works, though. I'm going to keep digging, but was hoping someone would know the answer or lead me in the right direction.
",{},{}
