15005,IssuesEvent,2016-03-01 15:34:27+00:00,9952134,python-visualization/folium,4586863,BibMartin,9969242,python-visualization,closed,Reuse of custom icons,[],[],1,"This is fantastic - makes visualisation so much easier.  

I have been playing with custom icons.  I don't seem to be able to reuse a custom icon - doing so simply shows the default blue icon in the first location and nothing in subsequent ones.

The code I used is as follows:

```python
import folium
g_icon_image = ""http://leafletjs.com/docs/images/leaf-green.png""
r_icon_image = ""http://leafletjs.com/docs/images/leaf-red.png""
o_icon_image = ""http://leafletjs.com/docs/images/leaf-orange.png""
shadow_image = ""http://leafletjs.com/docs/images/leaf-shadow.png""

map = folium.Map([51.5, -0.09], zoom_start=13)
g = folium.features.CustomIcon(g_icon_image,
                                icon_size=(38, 95),
                                icon_anchor=(22, 94),
                                shadow_image=shadow_image,
                                shadow_size=(50, 64),
                                shadow_anchor=(4, 62),
                                popup_anchor=(-3, -76))

r = folium.features.CustomIcon(r_icon_image,
                                icon_size=(38, 95),
                                icon_anchor=(22, 94),
                                shadow_image=shadow_image,
                                shadow_size=(50, 64),
                                shadow_anchor=(4, 62),
                                popup_anchor=(-3, -76))

o = folium.features.CustomIcon(o_icon_image,
                                icon_size=(38, 95),
                                icon_anchor=(22, 94),
                                shadow_image=shadow_image,
                                shadow_size=(50, 64),
                                shadow_anchor=(4, 62),
                                popup_anchor=(-3, -76))

o2 = folium.features.CustomIcon(o_icon_image,
                                icon_size=(38, 95),
                                icon_anchor=(22, 94),
                                shadow_image=shadow_image,
                                shadow_size=(50, 64),
                                shadow_anchor=(4, 62),
                                popup_anchor=(-3, -76))

mk = folium.map.Marker([51.5, -0.09], icon=g, popup=folium.map.Popup('Hello'))
mk3 = folium.map.Marker([51.49, -0.1], icon=o, popup=folium.map.Popup('orange'))
mk4 = folium.map.Marker([51.485, -0.15], icon=o2, popup=folium.map.Popup('orange 2'))
mk2 = folium.map.Marker([51.495, -0.083], icon=r, popup=folium.map.Popup('Goodbye'))
#mk5 = folium.map.Marker([51.487, -0.095], icon=r, popup=folium.map.Popup('red 2'))
map.add_children(mk)
map.add_children(mk2)
map.add_children(mk3)
map.add_children(mk4)
#map.add_children(mk5)

map
```

With the mk5 lines commented out, this works as expected (though I'm not sure whether it is intended to have to define a second orange custom icon [o2] to be able to show it on the map).  Reusing the red custom icon (by uncommenting mk5) leaves only the green marker rendered.  The rest become a single default icon.

Let me know if you need more information.  
Thanks
Chris",{},{}
