15279,IssuesEvent,2018-04-20 09:08:49+00:00,103890505,ConsenSys/mythril,5194767,b-mueller,10818037,ConsenSys,closed,Fix issues with the contract database,"[{'id': 695308630, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ConsenSys/mythril/labels/help%20wanted', 'name': 'help wanted', 'color': '33aa3f', 'default': True}]","[{'login': 'birdofpreyru', 'id': 20144632, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/20144632?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/birdofpreyru', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/birdofpreyru', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/birdofpreyru/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/birdofpreyru/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/birdofpreyru/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/birdofpreyru/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/birdofpreyru/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/birdofpreyru/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/birdofpreyru/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/birdofpreyru/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/birdofpreyru/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"Recently, multi-threading was added to the db initialization feature. Users are reporting bugs in the sync process:

- #110 The --init-db command will hang / fail to progress around the ~1000 unique contract mark
- #113 DB initializing crashes once the blocknumber approaches zero

Gitter use Ruide reports:

""I find out in the beginning of --init-db, the database has only a few contracts, so even for 8 threads, the memory usage is not high. like around 1~2gb. When there are over 3000 contracts in the database, the memory needed for 2 threads turn out to be over 10gb.""

See also the [discussion on Gitter](https://gitter.im/ConsenSys/mythril).

The task is to implement fixes for both issues. Issue a) should be a simple fix. Possible fixes for issue b) are making the number of threads configurable, or implementing automatic management of the thread count.
