15540,IssuesEvent,2018-07-19 05:40:25+00:00,32944298,Z3Prover/z3,449990,rixed,11668813,Z3Prover,opened,Strange behavior maybe related to rationals,[],[],0,"Looking at the VMs scheduling problems in https://rise4fun.com/Z3/tutorialcontent/optimization#h25
and more specifically at the integer encoded version, I though that this:

```smt
(assert (<= (+ (* 100 x11) (* 50 x21) (* 15 x31)) (* 100 y1)))
(assert (<= (+ (* 100 x12) (* 50 x22) (* 15 x32)) (* 75 y2)))
(assert (<= (+ (* 100 x13) (* 50 x23) (* 15 x33)) (* 200 y3)))
```

could as well have been written:

```smt
(assert (<= (+ (* 100 x11) (* 50 x21) (* 15 x31)) 100))
(assert (<= (+ (* 100 x12) (* 50 x22) (* 15 x32)) 75))
(assert (<= (+ (* 100 x13) (* 50 x23) (* 15 x33)) 200))
```

since `y{1,2,3}` will be either 0 or 1.

The result (on mater branch at 8744c62fca91dddc) is:

```
sat
(model 
  (define-fun y1 () Int
    0)
  (define-fun x13 () Int
    0)
  (define-fun x23 () Int
    0)
  (define-fun x33 () Int
    0)
  (define-fun y3 () Int
    0)
  (define-fun x12 () Int
    0)
  (define-fun y2 () Int
    0)
  (define-fun x32 () Int
    0)
  (define-fun x22 () Int
    0)
  (define-fun x31 () Int
    1)
  (define-fun x21 () Int
    1)
  (define-fun x11 () Int
    1)
)
(objectives
 ((+ y1 y2 y3) 1)
 ((+ (* 10 y1) (* 5 y2) (* 20 y3)) (/ 460.0 33.0))
)
```

Which seems to violates `(assert (and (>= y1 x11) (>= y1 x21) (>= y1 x31)))` but the result of the `((+ (* 10 y1) (* 5 y2) (* 20 y3))` objective seems to suggest there is more to `y{1,2,3}` value than what's in the model.

Is this normal and am I merely (or ignorant not_awake stupid) ?",{},{}
15542,IssuesEvent,2018-07-06 11:44:21+00:00,32944298,Z3Prover/z3,40890145,Koelbl,11668813,Z3Prover,opened,Ignore assert-soft while parsing,[],[],0,"Hello,
