15663,IssuesEvent,2018-03-15 09:52:22+00:00,70920962,PyFilesystem/pyfilesystem2,554369,willmcgugan,11898830,PyFilesystem,closed,fs.path.join breaks URLs,[],[],1,"`fs.path.join` coalesces slashes, which breaks protocol declarations if passed a URL. I'm not sure if it _should_ be URL-aware, but it should probably be consistent with `fs.path.combine`:

```
fs.path.join('smb://user:pass@host/svc','path')
'smb:/user:pass@host/svc/path'
# open_fs will treat this as an OS path

fs.path.combine('smb://user:pass@host/svc','path')
'smb://user:pass@host/svc/path'
# open_fs will treat this as a SMB path
```",{},{}
15673,IssuesEvent,2015-06-21 19:16:22+00:00,22783065,project-generator/project_generator,2963726,0xc0170,11992191,project-generator,closed,Virtual dir (group_name) consolidate,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/project-generator/project_generator/labels/type:%20feature', 'name': 'type: feature', 'color': '84b6eb'}]",[],1,"This might help to implement #146, the key can be only once, the code illustrates the problem:

```
projects:
  first_project:
    common:
      group_name:
        - name
     sources:
       - file.c
       - file2.cpp
```
For all sources, only  one virtual dir. It would probably be bettter to group sources:

```
projects:
  first_project:
    common:
      sources:
        group_one: #virtual dir, all files below in the list belong to this group
          - file.c
        group_two: #virtual dir
          - file2.cpp
```
