16436,IssuesEvent,2017-08-14 15:07:15+00:00,43852872,PulpQE/pulp-smash,9053044,kersommoura,14839747,PulpQE,opened,"Importers - As an authenticated user, I can use REST API to operate actions on an importer ","[{'id': 294019786, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/PulpQE/pulp-smash/labels/Issue%20Type:%20Test%20Case', 'name': 'Issue Type: Test Case', 'color': 'bfd4f2', 'default': False}, {'id': 639323840, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/PulpQE/pulp-smash/labels/Pulp%20Version:%203', 'name': 'Pulp Version: 3', 'color': 'd93f0b', 'default': False}]",[],0,"**For release pulp3 release alpha the file plugin will be the only available for tests.**

-     Create an importer
-     Read an importer
-     Update all mutable importer fields
-     Delete an importer (asynchronous)
-     Configure attributes on an Importer, such as:

```

    1.  validate (bool) [optional: defaults to True]: If true, the plugin will validate imported content.
    2.  ssl_ca_certificate (str) [optional] String containing a PEM encoded CA certificate used to validate the server certificate presented by the external source.
    3.  ssl_client_certificate (str) [optional] Contains a PEM encoded client certificate used for authentication.
    4.  ssl_client_key (str) [optional] Contains a PEM encoded private key used for authentication.
    5.  ssl_validation (bool) [optional: defaults to True]: If true, SSL peer validation must be performed.
    6.  proxy_url (str) [optional] Contains the proxy URL. Format: scheme://user:password@host:port.
    7.  username (str) [optional] Contains the username to be used for authentication when syncing.
    8.  password (str) [optional] Contains the password to be used for authentication when syncing.
    9.  download_policy (str) [optional] Contains the downloading policy name. This is a choice of three options:
      - immediate (default) - Downloading occurs during sync. The sync task does not complete until downloading is done.
      - background - Downloading is started by the sync but occurs in the background. The sync task completes before downloading is complete.
      - on-demand - The sync task records everything that would be downloaded but does not download content. Downloading occurs on demand as driven by client requests for content.
    10.  feed_url (str) [optional] Contains the URL of an external content source. This is optional.
    11.  sync mode: (str) [optional]. It has two choices 'additive' and 'mirror':
      - additive (default) - all remote content is added to the local repository on sync. During sync no content is removed from the local repository.
      - mirror - the local content will mirror the remote content exactly, removing local content if not also present in the remote content.
    12.  name (str) [required] Contains the name.
    13.  last_updated (datetime) [read-only] Contains the datetime of the last importer update.
    14.  last_synced (datetime) [read-only] Contains the datetime of the last importer sync.
    15.  max_count (int) - ???
```
",{},{}
