```
import torch
import retro

```

Running _test.py_ causes a crash. There is no error message of note, I just get a ""Python has stopped working"" window with a single ""Close program"" button. If I end the _Windows problem reporting_ task from the task manager before this window appears, I get an _Application Error_ window reporting a memory access violation. I am not sure if this is what causes the crash or if this is caused by killing the problem reporting task.

