16743,IssuesEvent,2018-02-08 17:06:49+00:00,55808787,openthread/openthread,16142208,jwhui,16142269,openthread,closed,[efr32] otPlatRadioTxDone not being called,"[{'id': 397568864, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/openthread/openthread/labels/P3', 'name': 'P3', 'color': 'DFDF00', 'default': False}, {'id': 355043111, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/openthread/openthread/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'ee0701', 'default': True}, {'id': 591811420, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/openthread/openthread/labels/platform:%20efr32', 'name': 'platform: efr32', 'color': 'fbca04', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'tomas-c', 'id': 5213953, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/5213953?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tomas-c', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/tomas-c', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tomas-c/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tomas-c/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tomas-c/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tomas-c/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tomas-c/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tomas-c/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tomas-c/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tomas-c/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tomas-c/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",5,"In some of the larger networks wpantund started printing ""STATUS_NOMEM"" errors. After this happens, the devices become leaders and form one device partitions. Checking the status of application buffers shows they are all being used for transmission and are not being released.

I made the modifications to radio.c to debug the problems. I have attached the diff at the bottom (the line numbers might not match exactly as I have more log messages, not shown here).

What I noticed is that at some point otPlatRadioTxDone is never called. Wpantund gets stuck printing
`NCP => [CRIT]-PLAT----: TX taking > 1000ms` (the log message I added) every second.

OpenThread version: 68a605f22e579ae45ab1d8221faa2d45e8668e05
Wpantund version: bcee1206c3e73b82f5e5cb16e624bd83b0114ffa

```C++
@@ -83,6 +83,9 @@ static otRadioFrame   sTransmitFrame;
 static uint8_t        sTransmitPsdu[IEEE802154_MAX_LENGTH];
 static otError        sTransmitError;
 
