17078,IssuesEvent,2016-12-27 14:54:00+00:00,63484632,facebookresearch/fastText,10478219,EdouardGrave,16943930,facebookresearch,closed,Supervised model with sub-word features,[],[],1,"Is there currently a way to train a supervised model using sub-word features?  Eg with nonzero `minn` and `maxn`?  I looked through the code and it looks like `getNgrams` never gets called in the `supervised` model -- only in the `cbow` and `skipgram` models.  Is there a particular reason for this?  Or some workaround?

If it's not possible, I may look into implementing myself

Thanks

EDIT: Obviously, you could preprocess the data into character n-grams, but I'd prefer not to have to do that if possible..",{},{}
17089,IssuesEvent,2018-02-22 11:06:08+00:00,94195575,cevoaustralia/aws-google-auth,540954,stevemac007,17036633,cevoaustralia,closed,"RuntimeError: Could not find SAML response, check your credentials",[],[],1,"While using aws-google-auth from ec2 instances with various ip I've encountered some cases not yet handled :

```
aws-google-auth --idp-id C01234567 --sp-id 123456789012 -u xxxx.xxxx@example.com -p default
Google Password: 
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""/usr/bin/aws-google-auth"", line 11, in <module>
    load_entry_point('aws-google-auth==0.0.20', 'console_scripts', 'aws-google-auth')()
  File ""/usr/lib/python2.7/site-packages/aws_google_auth/__init__.py"", line 54, in main
    cli(sys.argv[1:])
