17124,IssuesEvent,2017-09-19 18:24:42+00:00,53002916,httplib2/httplib2,1371800,bpaczkowski,17128733,httplib2,opened,Confusing response status types,[],[],0,"In the response class, we can observe this inconsistent behavior:

```
type(response)            # <class 'httplib2.Response'>
type(response.status)     # <class 'int'>
type(response['status'])  # <class 'str'>
```

I just spent half an hour debugging this before I finally looked into httplib2 source [here](https://github.com/httplib2/httplib2/blob/master/python3/httplib2/__init__.py#L1382). This piece of code seems to have been there for 12 years, may I ask what is the reason behind it?",{},{}
