17152,IssuesEvent,2017-06-13 17:32:10+00:00,51442999,python-cmd2/cmd2,2812720,tleonhardt,17161025,python-cmd2,opened,Add ability to pass arguments to a Python script,"[{'id': 324131052, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/python-cmd2/cmd2/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}]",[],0,"The **py** command supports running a Python script via ""py run('script.py')"".  However, it does not currently support the ability to pass any arguments to the script.

