17404,IssuesEvent,2016-11-10 22:41:05+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,6504915,bmw,17889013,certbot,opened,Rewrite our Dockerfile,"[{'id': 149596829, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/certbot/certbot/labels/Good%20Volunteer%20Task', 'name': 'Good Volunteer Task', 'color': 'fef2c0', 'default': False}, {'id': 276667632, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/certbot/certbot/labels/pkging', 'name': 'pkging', 'color': '000000', 'default': False}]",[],0,"Our current Dockerfile was largely written roughly 6 months before Let's Encrypt entered beta and it was a convenient way to test the project on different systems. It's in need of an update. I propose we update our Dockerfile to do the following:

* Continue installing from our repo rather than OS packages
* Remove unneeded OS dependencies after installing Certbot (such as `gcc`?)
* Clean `pip` cache after installing `certbot` (or don't use it all)
* Don't install the Apache or Nginx plugins

The resulting image should be roughly the size if we simply installed the `certbot` OS package. If this isn't possible for some reason, we may have to choose a different approach.",{},{}
