17576,IssuesEvent,2017-07-14 17:56:10+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,55078,ulope,19666847,raiden-network,opened,Argument mismatch between RestAPI.leave() and RaidenAPI.leave_token_network(),"[{'id': 318426945, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/raiden-network/raiden/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}, {'id': 473078399, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/raiden-network/raiden/labels/needs%20discussion', 'name': 'needs discussion', 'color': 'f9d0c4', 'default': False}]",[],0,"## Problem Definition

`RestAPI.leave()` calls `RaidenAPI.leave_token_network()` with the arguments `token_address`, `wait_for_settle` and `timeout` yet it only takes `token_address`.

## Solution

Decide whether these parameters are needed. Then either remove them from the Rest-API or add them to the Raiden-API.

## Tasklist

- [ ] Decide if parameters are needed
- [ ] Implement decision",{},{}
17577,IssuesEvent,2018-03-29 15:57:39+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,310139,hackaugusto,19666847,raiden-network,opened,Use different database paths for blockchains,[],[],0,"Raiden must not assume that the running blockchain client is always connected to the same network. Raiden can handle different networks by:

1. notifying the user about the mismatch and quitting 
2. using different database paths for different networks

The first option is a bit problematic because it makes unecessarily annoying to use different networks, so I propose the use of option 2 with a message on the command line about the current used network.",{},{}
