18265,IssuesEvent,2017-03-23 16:23:21+00:00,1248263,novnc/websockify,6640916,CendioOssman,24572588,novnc,closed,Routing to other websockify instances,[],[],1,"Apologies if this is not the place to post this question. If so, let me know and I'll delete and post in the appropriate forum.

I'm aware that the canonical use of websockify is to except a websocket connection and act as a bridge to a normal TCP socket connection.

However, I'm looking at a situation where I would like to use websockify's routing capabilities (meaning that websockify can't be on the same machine as the VNC server), but would also like use wss to encrypt right up to the machine hosting the VNC server (meaning that websockify has to be on the machine running the VNC server). 

Is there a way to that webockify can be used to route (I'm using a routing plugin that queries a database) to another websockify instance, which then performs the ""websocket bridge"" part of websockify's functionality?",{},{}
