18419,IssuesEvent,2017-06-19 10:43:06+00:00,4087724,dedupeio/dedupe,7846153,Leobouloc,27521766,dedupeio,closed,Iteration not possible in blockedSample while loop ?,[],[],4,"I believe [this line](https://github.com/dedupeio/dedupe/blob/master/dedupe/sampling.py#L43) will always return an empty list (because new_sample will allways be an empty generator), making the while loop useless possibly resulting in a lower number of blocked samples than requested. Is this correct or did I miss something?

```
def blockedSample(sampler, sample_size, predicates, *args) :
    
    blocked_sample = set()
    remaining_sample = sample_size - len(blocked_sample)
    previous_sample_size = 0

    while remaining_sample and predicates :
        [...]

         # -->  new_sample is a generator
        new_sample = sampler(remaining_sample, 
                             predicates,
                             *args)

         # -->  filtered_sample is a generator that uses all values from new_sample
        filtered_sample = (subsample for subsample 
                           in new_sample if subsample)

         # -->  The update uses all values from filtered_sample and therefore from new_sample
        blocked_sample.update(itertools.chain.from_iterable(filtered_sample))

        [...]
        
        # --> predicates is always ""[]"" since new_sample is always empty
        predicates = [pred for pred, pred_sample 
                      in zip(predicates, new_sample)
                      if pred_sample or pred_sample is None]
```",{},{}
