18449,IssuesEvent,2017-10-08 13:53:39+00:00,71948498,localstack/localstack,1752370,vangorra,28732122,localstack,closed,S3 create bucket policy not returning XML,"[{'id': 468888567, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/localstack/localstack/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'ee0701', 'default': True}, {'id': 577894037, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/localstack/localstack/labels/upstream-issue', 'name': 'upstream-issue', 'color': '0e8a16', 'default': False}]",[],2,"I'm using node to set the policy document of an S3 bucket hosted in localstack. I noticed when setting the policy document, neither XML nor JSON is returned. Only ""True"".

Running this in node:
``` javascript
const r = new AWS.S3().putBucketPolicy({
  Bucket: 'bucketName',
  Policy: JSON.stringify({
    Version: '2012-10-17',
    Statement: [
      Action: [ 's3:GetObject' ],
      Effect: 'Allow',
      Resource: 'arn:aws:s3:::bucketName/*',
      Principal: { AWS: [ '*' ] }
    ]
  }),
});

// This is where we see the raw HTTP Response. It's ""True"".
r.on('httpDone', (response: any) => {
  console.log('HTTP Response', response.httpResponse.body.toString());
});

await r.promise();
```

Produces this error:
```
XMLParserError: Non-whitespace before first tag.
Line: 0
Column: 1
Char: T
```
Notice how the string ""True"" is trying to be parsed as XML. The aws node api assume the response will be XML. So it should probably be provided.

I would expect the service to return valid XML. That would be consistent with the rest of the AWS API.",{},{}
