18508,IssuesEvent,2017-09-20 15:55:18+00:00,91284550,studioml/studio,1184005,karlmutch,30937953,studioml,closed,GPU Memory Requirements,"[{'id': 605103962, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/studioml/studio/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'ee0701', 'default': True}]","[{'login': 'karlmutch', 'id': 1184005, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/1184005?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/karlmutch', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/karlmutch', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/karlmutch/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/karlmutch/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/karlmutch/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/karlmutch/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/karlmutch/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/karlmutch/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/karlmutch/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/karlmutch/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/karlmutch/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",1,Right now the assumption is hard coded in get_available_gpus() from gpu_util.py that 90% of the total gpu memory is avaliable. This leads to problems when running locally where other processes may use gpu memory. We should change this to a explicit requirement for certain amount of GPU memory. ,{},{}
