18535,IssuesEvent,2018-07-09 23:04:17+00:00,102692863,onnx/onnx,40693,philtomson,31675368,onnx,opened,Improve the conv op testcase,[],[],0,"Apparently, currently the conv testcase uses a kernel with all 1's. When we were working on an ONNX importer for Julia's Flux framework we noticed we were getting mediocre results from imported trained models with conv ops. Turns out that the Flux framework is doing a cross-correlation by default whereas the imported (via ONNX) model had used convolution for training - there's not a lot of difference between the two ops and it really wouldn't matter which you used when training was done - **so long as the choice was consistent.** However interpretations between frameworks seem to differ - in our case we needed to flip the kernel matrix.

Since the ONNX conv op testcase uses the same value (1) for each entry in it's test kernel this kind of thing isn't detected. It would be better to change it so that each entry in the kernel is using a different value so that the tests can detect this ""flipped"" case.",{},{}
