18790,IssuesEvent,2012-02-20 08:33:22+00:00,3342046,RDFLib/rdflib,16417,gjhiggins,1401847,RDFLib,opened,Easy-to-download documentation,[],[],0,"denilsonsa, 2010-09-02T00:58:15.000Z
<pre>
I wanted to have local copy of the documentation, so I could read that offline. However, the only way of doing that is getting a SVN checkout, going into docs/ and then running make.

I was expecting to just have a downloadable tarball (or ZIP) with generated documentation. Or, even easier, documentation already included at the rdflib tarball.

Comment 1 by gjhigg...@gmail.com
In the interim, I have made available tarballs of the rendered versions of the sphinx docs and the epydoc api docs see:

http://groups.google.com/group/rdflib-dev/files


Comment 3 by gromgull
http://code.google.com/p/rdflib/downloads/detail?name=rdflib-docs-snapshot-20110827.tgz&can=2&q=#makechanges

I'll try to remember to upload a version with each release as well.
</pre>",{},{}
